UID:KEqMj604s2FZSqb4hjY0H
SUMMARY:Homebuyer Education Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260408T030258Z
DTSTART:20260411T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:This is a free five-hour workshop to help you meet the WA State
	 Housing Finance Commission’s education requirements for down payment assi
	stance and a variety of affordable housing programs and opportunities for 
	qualified applicants! These requirements include the successful completion
	 of a Homebuyers Education Seminar meeting the current FHA\, Fannie Mae\, 
	FreddieMac\, and SMBA benchmark standards.  \n\nAt the conclusion of the w
	orkshop\, participants will receive a certificate of achievement from the 
	WA State Housing Finance Commission and DFI valid for two years from the d
	ate of issuance.  \n\nTo join our next workshop\, please complete and subm
	it the following registration form at least 24-hours before your selected 
	workshop date. Once this form has been submitted\, be sure to check your e
	mail for a digital confirmation\, as well as additional follow up and impo
	rtant information from a ULMS Housing Department staff member.   \n\nIn-pe
	rson workshops are held every 1st and 2nd Saturday of the month from 10:00
	AM – 3:30PM. They will be held at our Main Office at the following address
	: 105 14th Ave\, Suite 200 Seattle\, WA 98122.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity
	.com/events/#/details/homebuyer-education-workshop/17282958/2026-04-11T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/homebuyer-education-works
	hop/17282958/2026-04-11T00
